    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="877"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d877">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 704.9312/3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The request of the Chinese chargé d’affaires at Mexico City, as reported in your
                    telegram of the 8th instant, was communicated to the <pb facs="0698" n="616"
                        xml:id="pg_616"/> Department of Commerce and Labor, and that department has
                    sent the following instruction to the immigration inspector at El Paso: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>In case attack upon Juárez permit Chinese enter El Paso under hest
                            possible arrangements to insure prompt return on cessation hostilities
                            there.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
